cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "MAKER Framework"
abstract: >-
  MAKER (Massively decomposed Agentic processes with K-margin Error Reduction)
  is a Rust library and MCP server for zero-error long-horizon LLM agent
  execution. It implements SPRT-based voting, red-flag validation, and
  microagent orchestration to achieve mathematically-grounded error correction
  for LLM agents.
version: "0.3.0"
date-released: "2026-02-27"
license: MIT
url: "https://github.com/zircote/maker-rs"
